*/
Problem 2181. Merge Node in Between zeroes.
Platform-Leetcode
Difficulty-Medium
Frequency-7ms
Approach-
Create a dummy node to build the result list.
Traverse the linked list.
Maintain a variable sum to store values between zeros.
When a 0 is found:
If sum exists, create a new node with that sum.
Attach it to the result list.
Reset sum.
Ignore zero values while adding.
Return the next node of dummy.
Soution-*/
class Solution {
    public ListNode mergeNodes(ListNode head) {
        ListNode x=new ListNode(-1);
        ListNode tail=x;
        int sum=0,count=0;
        while(head!=null){
            if(head.val==0){
                if(count>0){
                    tail.next=new ListNode(sum);
                    tail=tail.next;
                }
                sum=0; count++;
            }
            else if(count>0){
                sum+=head.val;
            }
            head=head.next;
        }
        return x.next;
    }
}
